==English==

===Noun===
'''freak'''  (''plural:'' '''[[freaks]]''')
# A [[sudden]] causeless [[change]] or turn of the [[mind]]; a whim of fancy; a capricious prank; a [[vagary]] or [[caprice]].
# ''(of a person):'' an oddball; too unique
# {{bodybuilding}}: A person whose [[physique]] has grown far beyond the normal limits of [[muscular]] development; often a [[bodybuilder]] weighing more than 120 kilos (260 pounds). It can also mean a person whose physical features are, in some way, deformed or displeasing.
# A person who has an obsession or extreme knowledge of a something.

====Derived terms====
*[[freak of nature]]
*[[freaky]]

===Verb===
'''to freak'''  ''(often with '''[[out]]''')''  ([[freaks]], [[freaked]], [[freaking]])
#To [[variegate]]; to [[checker]]; to [[streak]].

